what is gerd and what is the cure gerd is a short word for gastroesophageal reflux disease meaning you have acid reflux this condition can cause erosions in your esophagus and ulcers along with other conditions a lot of times doctors will prescribe a medication to help with the acid your stomach makes such as nexium aciphex omeprazole available over the counter as prilosec or protonix there is no cure for this condition the medications will help keep your symptoms under control nausea burning sensation in chest etc since you have access to the internet look it up and do some research the more educated you are on your condition the better you will able to treat it Gastroesophageal reflux disease Heartburn Proton pump inhibitor Helicobacter pylori Esomeprazole Stomach cancer Esophageal cancer Peptic ulcer Esophagus Gastroparesis Achalasia Asthma Chest pain H2-receptor antagonist Psoriasis Cancer of the larynx Ulcerative colitis Ranitidine Cancer Barrett's esophagus Mouth ulcer Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Osteoarthritis Obesity Diabetes mellitus Migraine Kevin Trudeau Urinary incontinence Medicine Tuberculosis Clinical depression Adjustable gastric band Metoclopramide Prostate cancer Emphysema Homeopathy Parkinson's disease Pneumonia Reflux Aspartame Coeliac disease Acupuncture Esophagogastroduodenoscopy Bipolar disorder Sulfasalazine Obstetrics Mastocytosis Caffeine First aid Tobacco smoking Radiation therapy AIDS Colorectal cancer Glossary of medical terms related to communications disorders Narcolepsy Cannabis (drug) Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Fibromyalgia Spina bifida Chronic fatigue syndrome Crohn's disease Cirrhosis Lupus erythematosus Antidepressant Acne Diarrhea Vomiting Epilepsy Diabetic neuropathy Stomach Halitosis Transsexuality Aloe Dermatology Hiatus hernia Conjunctivitis Ebola Anxiety Medical prescription Eczema Quackery Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug Multiple sclerosis Growth hormone treatment Panic attack Traumatic brain injury Beh__et's 